saevitiam centurionum et vaca- tiones munerum: both expressions de- note the same practice. If centurions knew that a soldier had money to spate, they laid additional tasks on him to make him purchase furlough or exemp- tion. A full description of this system, and of the demoralisation resulting from it, is given in H. 1. 86.
